President Obama and Prime Minister Cameron had a phone call to discuss global issues, including the hostage situation in Algeria. They expressed support for France's efforts to prevent terrorists from finding a safe haven in Mali. Prime Minister Cameron also discussed his thoughts on UK-EU relations, which he would be addressing in an upcoming speech. The President emphasized the close alliance between the US and the UK and expressed the importance of a strong UK within a strong European Union, as it contributes to peace, prosperity, and security in Europe and worldwide.